1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:08,011
Deep Research can return dozens of sources, careful citations, and pages of polished prose, yet still leave you unsure what to do.

2
00:00:07,961 --> 00:00:14,538
The failure often begins before the search: the request names a topic, but not the decision the research must support.

3
00:00:14,538 --> 00:00:20,471
OpenAI Academy describes research as a path from questions to evidence-backed insights and decisions.

4
00:00:20,471 --> 00:00:32,500
Its guidance separates fast Search from multi-step Deep Research, and recommends an outline, sub-questions, a source strategy, evaluation criteria, citations, and an explicit account of what is still missing.

5
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,201
Those pieces point to a better way to ask.

6
00:00:35,201 --> 00:00:38,721
Do not send a vague topic into a powerful research tool.

7
00:00:38,721 --> 00:00:47,125
Give it a compact contract that defines the decision, the scope, the evidence standard, the gaps it must expose, and the shape of the final deliverable.

8
00:00:47,125 --> 00:00:51,653
In this video, we will build that contract as a Decision-Ready Research Brief.

9
00:00:51,653 --> 00:01:03,326
You will learn how to choose the right research depth, turn one decision into a scoped plan, judge evidence instead of merely collecting links, surface uncertainty, and request an output that can actually move work forward.

10
00:01:03,326 --> 00:01:08,500
Keep one principle in view: good research is not measured by how much material it gathers.

11
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:14,826
It is measured by whether another person can inspect the evidence, understand the limits, and make the next decision.
